The paper deals with the analysis of egocentric photostreams, which involves computer vision techniques such as object recognition, scene understanding, and image classification, suggesting that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of wearable cameras, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The study aims to understand the effect of egocentric images on an observer, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a method for sentiment analysis, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
